<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="497" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,887,1525]" pageId="3" pageNumber="497">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1391,1416]" pageId="3" pageNumber="497">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="" authorityYear="1918" baseAuthorityName="Distant" box="[594,725,1392,1416]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Balclutha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sternalis">
<emphasis box="[594,725,1392,1416]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="497">B. sternalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vilbaste" authorityYear="1968" box="[783,930,1392,1416]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Balclutha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="versicolor">
<emphasis box="[783,930,1392,1416]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="497">B. versicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in color and external characters, but can be distinguished from them and other species by the dorsal apodeme and socle of the aedeagus having paired processes, the very long subgenital plate, and the attenuate, spinelike pygofer apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1133,1500,1525]" pageId="3" pageNumber="497" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,887,1525]" box="[199,1133,1500,1525]" pageId="3" pageNumber="497">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1500,1525]" pageId="3" pageNumber="497">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name “longispina” refers to the long pygofer caudal spine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
